<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--LuxuryBus     08-03 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Luxury Bus,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Luxury Bus Starts Service</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A luxury commuter bus that features a
bathroom, kitchen and a cellular phone has begun running to
downtown San Francisco.
   ``It's kind of like being on vacation,'' said financial
consultant Jim Chisolm, one of the passengers aboard the Execucoach
for its inaugural trip into the city Tuesday. ``This is actually
nicer than my office.''
   Execucoach Inc. President Mark Wixom thinks executives are
willing to pay the introductory price of $149.95 per month for the
service on the 40-seat bus _ about $40 more than the cost of riding
Golden Gate Transit.
   ``I think it's the same ideology that prompts somebody to buy a
Porsche instead of a Chevrolet,'' he said. ``They feel a need to
rise above the common man and become unique.''
   The $120,000 coach has smoked windows, a blue Naugahyde
dashboard, carpets, and a microwave oven. Newspapers, non-alcoholic
beverages and one-minute calls on the cellular phone are free.
</TEXT>
