which the House rejected an amendment to ban use of government
funds for abortions in the District of Columbia.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to impose the restrictions.
   Voting yes were 71 Democrats and 135 Republicans; voting no were
179 Democrats and 40 Republicans.
   Y is yes; N is no; X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
