<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0445</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chantal Remnants Wet Oklahoma, Texas; Thunderstorms Lash North Dakota</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms remaining from Hurricane Chantal posed
a threat of floods to parts of Oklahoma and Texas today, and
thunderstorms brought hurricane-force winds and heavy rains to
North Dakota.
   The remnants of Chantal spread rain from central Oklahoma to
southwest Texas, and a flash flood watch remained in effect for
much of western Oklahoma and a small portion of north-central Texas.
   Thunderstorms developed ahead of a cold front over the
north-central states Wednesday, with the strongest storms in North
Dakota during the evening. In the town of Lakota, winds gusted to
78 mph and 3.5 inches of rain fell.
   A thunderstorm also dropped 1.19 inches of rain at Brule, S.D.
   Showers and thunderstorms extended across northwestern Minnesota
and eastern North Dakota early today, and from eastern South Dakota
into eastern Colorado.
   Northeast Florida also was hit by thunderstorms Wednesday. High
winds downed trees at Bithlo and at Christmas.
   A few showers and thunderstorms also were scattered across the
Northeastern states.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms to be
scattered across the Gulf Coast states, the Plains, the upper half
of the Mississippi Valley and Upper Michigan, with storms most
numerous over Iowa, western Missouri, eastern Kansas and Oklahoma.
Showers and thunderstorms also were expected to be scattered over
northern New England and eastern New York state.
   Highs were expected to be in the 70s in the northern Rockies and
along the Pacific Coast; over 100 degrees in the Rio Grande Valley
of Texas; from 100 to 110 degrees in the Desert Southwest; and in
the 80s and 90s elsewhere.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 50 degrees at Burns,
Ore., to 94 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 fair; Boston 68 partly cloudy; Charleston,
S.C. 76 fair; Cincinnati 70 foggy; Cleveland 67 fair; Detroit 67
fair; Miami 81 partly cloudy; New York 69 showery; Philadelphia 72
cloudy; Pittsburgh 68 fair; Portland, Maine 65 cloudy; Washington,
D.C. 70 foggy.
   _Central: Birmingham 73 fair; Bismarck 80 fair; Chicago 75 hazy;
Denver 65 fair; Des Moines 76 partly cloudy; Indianapolis 67 foggy;
Kansas City 79 fair; Nashville 75 hazy; New Orleans 78 fair; St.
Louis 79 foggy; Minneapolis@St. Paul 79 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 69 fair; Anchorage 58 cloudy; Boise 61 fair;
Honolulu 77 fair; Las Vegas 85 fair; Los Angeles 64 fair; Phoenix
94 partly cloudy; Salt Lake City 78 fair; San Diego 68 partly
cloudy; San Francisco 60 cloudy; Seattle 61 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 66 partly cloudy; Toronto 73 fair.
