<SECOND>PM-Officer Shot,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Officer Shot to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>IRVINGTON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A police officer was killed early this
morning when a fellow officer's gun went off as police tried to
break down a door, the mayor said.
   Mayor J. Walter Jonkoski said officers were trying to force
their way into a building believed to be the center of a local drug
distribution ring when the shooting occurred at dawn.
   ``It's a real shame,'' the mayor said.
   The officer, from the Essex County Police Department, was taken
to University Hospital in Newark. His name was withheld.
   A hospital spokeswoman, Robin Preisler, said the officer arrived
at the hospital at about 6:20 a.m. and was pronounced dead at 6:40
a.m.
   Jonkoski said drugs are a constant problem in the neighborhood,
which borders Newark.
