<HEAD>Big Fire Rages Through Department Store</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf with 4 grafs to UPDATE with 27 hurt, other detail.
Pickup 3rd pvs, ``We fear ...''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through a crowded department
store in downtown Taipei on Thursday night, and authorities feared
that some shoppers may have been killed.
   The fire broke out shortly before 8 p.m. on the fifth floor of
the 10-story Fit Today department store, and initial reports said
27 people were injured, police said.
   A firefighter was seriously burned and 26 shoppers were
hospitalized for smoke inhalation, they said.
   Firefighters smashed windows to rescue shoppers and movie goers
trapped by thick smoke from the blaze, which they said probably
started in a restaurant. They brought the blaze under control after
four hours.
   ``We fear many people have suffocated ... in the building,''
said Wang Hua-cheng, Taipei's police deputy chief.
   Many shoppers escaped to the roof to wait for rescue by
helicopters.
