<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 221-199 roll call Thursday by
which the House passed and sent to the Senate landmark legislation
bailing out the savings and loan industry.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to approve the bill, including a
Democratic-backed financing plan that President Bush says will
undermine the Gramm-Rudman deficit-reduction law.
   Voting yes were 182 Democrats and 39 Republicans.
   Voting no were 67 Democrats and 132 Republicans.
   Y is yes. N is no. X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are 3 vacancies in the 435-member House.
