<HEAD>Kidnappers' Statement on Suspending Death Sentence</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 4th graf, If any ...INSERTING dropped word ``then.'' Picks
up 5th graf, `1. The ...'</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Hostages, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Following is the full text of the Arabic
statement issued by the Revolutionary Justice Organization,
suspending the killing of American hostage Joseph James Cicippio.
It was translated by The Associated Press bureau in Beirut:
   In the name of the almighty God,
   We would have wished a failure of diplomacy in order to execute
the spy Cicippio and drag the United States into the trap to
humiliate it anew and to remind it of the events of the year '83.
But out of respect for the intervention by the parties and states
with whom America pleaded to mediate and stop the execution, we
declare the freezing of the death sentence and its substitution
with an initiative.
   If any initiative would resolve the affair and reveal the
intentions and intrigues of the Zionist imperialism, then the
Revolutionary Justice Organization, the vanguard of humanitarian
initiatives, declares the following intiative:
   1. The release of Sheik (Abdul Karim) Obeid and a number of the
strugglers of the Palestinian intefadah and the heroes of the
Lebanese resistance against the Israeli occupation. The numbers and
lists of their names are to be prepared later and presented to the
Red Cross.
   2. Acceptance should be announced within days, otherwise the
initiative will be considered canceled.
   Victory to the downtrodden in the liberation march,
   Justice, glory and immortality to the martyrs,
   The Revolutionary Justice Organization.
</TEXT>
