<SECOND>AM-Britain-Explosion,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Explosion Rips Through London Hotel, Kills One</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion ripped through a small London hotel
Thursday, killing one person _ who apparently was responsible for
the blast _ and seriously damaging the five-story building, police
said.
   Buildings neighboring the Beverly House Hotel in central London
were evacuated and dogs searched the wrecked structure for any
further explosives, police said.
   It was not immediately clear what caused the explosion, but a
spokesman at Scotland Yard said the blast was believed to have
occurred in the room where the victim had been staying.
   Commander George Churchill-Coleman, head of Scotland Yard's
Anti-terrorist Squad, said the dead man was ``apparently
responsible'' for the explosion.
   Police said the dead man was of Middle Eastern origin but would
not release his identity. He was reported to have stayed for
several days in a fourth-floor room in the 18-room hotel.
   His body was found wedged between the second and third floors of
the hotel, police said.
