resolve the election. The opposition wants recognition of its
electoral victory and Gen. Noriega's departure from power.
   Noriega was indicted in Florida in February 1988 on drug
trafficking and money laundering charges, which he denied.
President Eric Delvalle tried to fire Noriega as Defense Forces
chief following the U.S. charges, but Noriega maneuvered to have
the National Assembly dismiss Delvalle, who the United States still
recognizes as president.
