<FIRST>u i AM-Italy-Kidnap     08-03 0339</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Kidnap,0350</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kidnapped Coffee King Rescued by Police</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police stormed a hillside hideout Thursday and
rescued a Florentine businessman who was kidnapped by Sardinian
bandits nine weeks ago.
   Dante Belardinelli, 62, dubbed the ``coffee king'' by the
Italian press, was found blindfolded in a tent with his leg chained
to a tree.
   The coffee product distributor was abducted on May 30 as he
drove to his Tuscan villa.
   Police said they arrested a Sardinian shepherd, Costantino
Pintore, 36, who was guarding the tent with a sawed-off shotgun.
The hideout lay near Manciano in a hilly coastal area about 62
miles northwest of Rome.
   Belardinelli, looking haggard but flashing the ``V'' for victory
sign, hugged one of his police rescuers. He was taken by helicopter
to Rome police headquarters and met reporters after being examined
by a doctor.
   ``I'm so happy to be here,'' he said.
   Slices of both his ears were found July 23 in an envelope in a
bar in Bologna, along with a photo and a ransom demand, reportedly
for $3.7 million dollars.
   On Saturday, police killed two kidnappers in a highway shootout,
after disguising themselves as Belardinelli's relatives on their
way to pay the ransom. Two bandits escaped and four policemen were
wounded.
   A Florence magistrate said he ordered the ransom money
confiscated so the family couldn't pay. The government said it was
pursuing a hard line with the kidnappers to try to end a plague of
abductions.
   Many of the abductions are blamed either on the Calabrian Mafia,
known as the 'ndrangheta, or on Sardinian gangs, who work out of
the island or from Sardinian communities in west central Italy.
   Belardinelli said he was kept blindfolded throughout his
captivity.
   ``When I heard the sound of the helicopter I thought, `They're
finally here,''' he said, near tears, ``I shouted `I'm here!' and
they said `Who?' and I said, `What do you mean who? Me,
Belardinelli!'''
   On Wednesday, police arrested three brothers in connection with
Belardinelli's abduction and for investigation into other
abductions.
</TEXT>
