<HEAD>Fireworks Explode, Killing Two Workers and Injuring Seven Others</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 350 fireworks accidentally exploded at the
same time on a barge off the port of Yokohoma, killing two
technicians and injuring seven others, police said Thursday.
   More than 100,000 spectators were watching an annual display
Wednesday night when one technician set off a charge on a skyrocket
aboard the 1,037-ton barge, berthed about 900 feet from a seafront
park, police said.
   They said the sudden blast ignited 350 other fireworks aboard
the barge. Police said those killed and wounded were fireworks
technicians.
   Kanagawa Prefectural Police spokesman Teruo Matoba said those
injured were taken by a coast guard boat to nearby hospitals in
Yokohama, 18 miles south of Tokyo, for treatment of burns and
bruises.
   Police were investigating.
