<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProduction     08-03 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Production,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
158,412 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
147,995, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 145,939 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 86,988 cars this week,
compared with 84,312 a week ago and 82,853 in the same week in 1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 71,424,
compared with last week's 63,683 and last year's 63,086.
   Canadian automakers were to build 12,029 cars this week, down
from 15,638 a week ago and up from last year's 6,162.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 8,845, compared
with 12,870 a week ago and 8,253 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
